e of our society's current fits and starts, those who most loudly condemn it in other people are also often its main practitioners.
\par But this fact does not protect }{\i\v\f0\fs24\lang2057 The Nation}{\v\f0\fs24\lang2057  from the accusation that its tribal composition is heavily biased in the direction
 of one tribe. That is a fact which nobody needs to be an enemy of The Nation to mention. We mention it again and again, not because we wish misfortune to that publishing house, but, on the contrary, only because we believe that that organization can oil 
the wheels of its production line only if it corrects the tribal imbalance now besetting it.
\par For this disease has been with it for a long time and is, therefore, quite a separate issue from the fact that some individuals, motivated by anti-Kikuyu tribalism, may be using devious methods to embarrass }{\i\v\f0\fs24\lang2057 The Nation}{
